It is well known that in the case of some diseases, such as Ebola (Nistal et al. 2019), the infective lying corpses are infective. The dead infective corpses can be considered in the model as a new sub-population D that can infect again. In this case, to extend our model, we add the parameter z - the probability of infection from corpses - to regulate the transition \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
